hopobject.body: Could you give me some smaller notes? precio duramale Clothing attire aside, Sanford wasn’t the only one breaking the decorum in the Speaker’s Lobby that day. One of the witnesses to the incident, referred to by RollCall as the “[Heard on the Hill] tipster,” snapped a couple photos of the shorts-wearing congressman in action, a move that is strictly prohibited in that part of the Capitol. The mystery photographer’s snapshot is largely unprecedented in the Speaker’s Lobby, where reporters cluster to meet with lawmakers and congressional aides.
